text: The state that gave the world flight, eight Presidents, the first person to walk on the moon, and the
label: BODY

text: nation's top 2002 college football team turns 200 on March 1.
label: BODY

text: On that day, the Ohio Bicentennial Commission kicks off an eight-month celebration with a day of
label: BODY

text: activities to celebrate Statehood Day. The day's events will take place in historic Chillicothe, the site
label: BODY

text: of the state capital when Ohio entered the Union in 1803.
label: BODY

text: Ohio will celebrate its 200th Birthday with a variety of activities, including a prayer breakfast, a
label: BODY

text: black-tie ball, a special joint session of the Ohio General Assembly, the re-creation of an 1803
label: BODY

text: village, the first day issuance of a U.S. Postal Service stamp recognizing Ohio statehood, and the
label: BODY

text: re-opening of Adena, the home of Thomas Worthington, recognized as the Father of Ohio Statehood.
label: BODY

text: Statehood Day is just the start of a months-long celebration that will reach every corner of Ohio.
label: BODY

text: Other activities will include a Tall Ships festival on the Lake Erie coastline in July, a re-enactment of
label: BODY

text: a wagon train cross the state in June and July, a riverboat festival on the Ohio River in October, and
label: BODY

text: a month-long celebration of the centennial of flight in Dayton in July. The celebration will also
label: BODY

text: include two days of fireworks, and entertainment in Columbus July 3-4.
label: BODY

text: These activities will happen on top of other projects that the Ohio Bicentennial Commission has
label: BODY

text: undertaken over the past several years. One ongoing project will see 250-pound bronze Bicentennial
label: BODY

text: Bells cast in 41 Ohio Counties. This project began in 2001 as a partnership between the Bicentennial
label: BODY

text: Commission and the Verdin Company of Cincinnati, Ohio's oldest family-owned manufacturer.
label: BODY

text: When completed, the project will have cast a personalized bell in each of Ohio's 88 counties during
label: BODY

text: Another enormously popular program has seen the Bicentennial Commission paint its logo on a
label: BODY

text: barn in each Ohio County. The barn paintings have become extremely popular, with hundreds of
label: BODY

text: Ohioans cris-crossing the state to visit and photograph all 88 barns.
label: BODY

label: BODY

text: plate in October 2001.  The ODPS sold 1,384,013 bicentennial plates in 2001.  In 2002, there
label: BODY

text: were 3,629, 611 plates sold.  More than 5 million plates
label: BODY

text: are now on the road advertising the bicentennial year.
